You find yourself dropped in the middle of a random world. 

Its your job to survive and conquer it.

You might start to notice things seem harder to craft, but you keep on going.
The basic beginning.

Tinkers construct lets you create tools that can mine diamonds, mine 3 by 3, and chop trees in one blow.
It is highly recommended you progress in this mod.

This is your first alloys. It requires burning fuel.

This is a 2 by 2 by 2 multiblock. Right click the hammer where you want it to face.
Time to upgrade to metal tools
The base block for forestry machines and heavy engineering blocks.
A machine made to squeeze fluids out of objects
No Description
No Description
This is the base tool of immersive engineering and helps you create multiblocks.
This is made from wood and creosote. A block used in many recipes.
This helps you create early game plate, rods and gears.

A very important material, made from iron and coal coke in the blast furnace.


I would recommend you start stocking up. :)
A machine that is used to make many recipes. Usually requires a fluid
A special type of infused stick made in the carpentar

This is a mod which helps you scan for ores in the earth, helpful for finding veins.

This pack has fairly large veins, so finding one would sustain you for a while.
Go to the nether. Gather some netherrack/nether brick and go kill some blazes.
The preheaters can be given power to make it faster.
When powered and placed next to a furnace, the furnace no longer requires fuel. The more there are, the faster the furnace runs.

This pack will not tell you which power sources to do. It is about exploration and seeing what works best for you.

Early game, immersive would be recommended.

Clearly you cannot sustain with a clockwork engine.

In immersive engineering, energy is carried around in wires. The wires are known as coils in JEI

Use the wire connectors to connect to power generators/capacitors and machines. Use the wires to connect them all.

Each tier can send more power, but the cable has to match the connector or it burns up.

Relays can be used send wires further.

Wires can be insulated or they will damage you.

Your first power, for the squeezer and carpentar.

Hold right click to load it and then release when it reaches red for a burst of power.

Stygian iron ore can be crafted using the YA HAMMER!

Easier methods will be obtainable later on.

Immersive has loads of multiblocks. This will help you visualize them and help you build them.

You only need to craft this once. Open the multiblock you want in your engineers manual and then combine the two items in the crafting grid

Use the manual to see how it works.
The Metal Press is one of the first multiblocks you should get. It will cut the costs of your plates and rods. And later, your gears as well.
The first ways to store power. Use the engineers hammer to toggle inputs and outputs.

A workbench that helps you create some items in the immersive engineering mod

If you start seeing visual glitches near the workbench, remove the blueprint and they should go away if the workbench caused them.
A crafting step item that is made in the engineers workbench.

Garden cloches are used to grow crops in a compact space.

They require power and water. They can take fertilizer such as forestry fertilizer or bone meal to speed up growth.

They have already been buffed in this pack.

You will need to build the squeezer.

This will create plant oil for you.

You will need to build the crusher multiblock to create coke dust.

This can also be used to ore double.

You will need to build the industrial fermenter for this. 

Sugarcane can turn into ethanol.
You will need to build a refinery and combine ethanol and plant oil to create biodiesel
This is a base material used in progression quite a bit.

A Whole New World
